snippet.title: Blueprint for the Black Joy Era | Jazmine "Da K.O.S." Walker & Amber Phillips | TEDxRVA
snippet.description:
Washington, D.C. based reproductive justice organizers, political commentators, and media makers, Amber J. Phillips and Jazmine Walker are the co-hosts and creators of the weekly podcast, The Black Joy Mixtape. Jazmine and Amber use the Black Joy Mixtape to center women, girls, and femmes as they tackle the weekly news and political headlines through comedy and sisterhood. Their talk defines what Black Joy is, barriers to its expression, and how Black Joy can energize our movements and all our lives. You've never heard a Tedx Talk or the news like this before!

Jazmine “The King of the South” Walker is a Southern Development Strategist supporting social justice organizations working in the Deep South and Central Appalachia. Growing up and earning a Master’s Degree in Sociology in Mississippi, her life and career have been deeply influenced by Southern rap & hip hop, leading her to connect thoughtful, comedic, and timely commentary on politics, news, culture, and movement organizing.

Amber J. Phillips is working to advance the rights of all Black people and people of color. Her writings on Black women at the intersections of politics, pop culture, and the media have been published on new sites like Huffington Post and Rewire, and she’s been featured as a leading voice for Black feminism on The Breakfast Club and ESSENCE. In addition to being the Senior Manager of Youth Leadership and Mobilization at Advocates for Youth, Amber is the Co-Director/Founder of the digital marketing firm, BLACK that uses culture to elevate Black progressive power in politics and media.

Their talk explores embracing Blackness and cultural pride for societal healing. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx

snippet.title: Amber Heard talks about career roadblocks due bisexual revelation
snippet.description:
Amber Heard talks about career roadblocks due bisexual revelation
‘Danish Girl’ starlet Amber Heard was shocked to see how coming out as bisexual in 2010, impacted her career.

Addressing the second annual Pride and Prejudice Summit in New York, Amber revealed the truth about her sexuality to a reporter.

&ldquo I just answered honestly,” she revealed in her interview that took place seven years ago. “I could tell by the look on this person’s face it was a big deal. My poor publicist! Then I realised the gravity of what I had done and why so many people -studio execs, agents, advisers -did not want this coming before my name. I became attached to a label. So, I watched as I quickly became not actress Amber Heard but out lesbian Amber Heard.”

The warnings given by Hollywood execs did carry some truth within about being stigmatised.

The thirty-year-old actress revealed how it affected her career, stating, “It did impact my career; it was difficult. It was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult; because no one had done it. I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career without a doubt.”

However, her confession was worth the entire struggle she went through. “I’ve never seen myself defined by the person I’m with. I saw myself being in this unique position and having a unique responsibility. So, I bit the bullet,” she stated.

Around that time, she had credits in Zombieland and Pineapple Express under her belt and she was on the rise.

“As a leading lady, there’s a certain amount of wish fulfilment. I was asked ‘How is anyone going to invest in you romantically if they think you’re unavailable?’” she recalled. “I said, ‘Watch me do it.’”

Amber dated artist and photographer Tasya van Ree at that time and they split in 2012, after four years of dating. She fell for The Rum Diary co-star Johnny Depp and they got married. “When I hear someone comment about me coming out, I think it’s funny because I was never in part because I was very stubborn, I guess, and also in part because I just didn’t feel it was wrong,” she commented.

She concluded, “I stand here now among many of my romantic leading lady peers who are out and fluid. I’m one of many now, and I’m working. If every gay man that I know personally in Hollywood came out tomorrow, then this would be a nonissue in a month. We have a long way to go.”

Last her, Heard finalised her divorce with Depp and lately, she’s been linked to billionaire Elon Musk.

snippet.title: Utah Amber Alert issued for two girls
snippet.description:
Utah Amber Alert issued for two girls

(KUTV) An Utah Amber Alert has been issued for two girls, 4 and 8 years old.
Police are looking for Elizabeth Dinah Coltharp, 8, and Hattie Briella Coltharp, 4. They are believed to be with Samuel Warren Shaffer, 34.
Police said Shaffer was seen with the two girls along with his own two daughters Lillie and Samantha Shaffer. They were seen on foot but it is not known if there is a vehicle involved.
2News will update this story as more information becomes available.
Elizabeth Cotharp, 8, is described as:
4 feet 9 inches tall
45 pounds
Brown hair
Brown eyes
Last seen wearing a blue dress, gray pants under the dress, wearning hiking books which are possibly camouflaged and a camouflaged jacked.
Hattie Briella Coltharp is 4, is described as:
2 feet 10 inches tall
37 pounds
Brown hair
Brown eyes
Last seen wearing blue spandex pants with purple polka dots and short sleeve shirt of an undetermined color
Suspected abductor Samual Warren Shaffer, 34, is described as:
5 feet 10 inches tall
160 pounds
Brown hair
Hazel eyes
Last seen wearing black pants, a black puffy coat, comouflaged boonie hat
A Facebook page called Help us find the Coltharps has information that KUTV can not verify but may be information useful to finding the missing children.
GRANTSVILLE, Utah (ABC4 Utah) An Amber Alert was canceled after it was issued for two girls age 7 and 11 outside Grantsville Wednesday afternoon.  
 
Officials said the girls were taken from 313 S. Cooley St. around 2:15 p.m. Investigators said the father was issued papers that gave temporary custody to the girls mother. When she went to pick them up they were gone.
 
The suspect and father of the children, 53 year old Kenneth Shrewsbury,  was eventually found in Magna. According to family he was visiting his mother when he heard about the alert.
 
According to Grantsville police, the father and mother are in a custody dispute. They said he voluntarily brought is daughters to a Unified Police Department substation in Magna. 
 
Shrewsbury was taken to the Tooele County Jail, but it's unclear what he will be charged with. The girls are back with their mother.

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland and The Joneses brought her further attention. She next starred in John Carpenter's The Ward, alongside Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and alongside Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary, for which she won a Spotlight Award at the Hollywood Film Festival. In 2014 she appeared in 3 Days to Kill, and in 2015 in Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl. She will play Mera in the upcoming superhero film, Justice League.

Nearbuy (formerly Groupon India) just got recognised among the first 10 companies in India to successfully engage employees and predict attrition using A.I. in HR. 

3 Challenges Nearbuy faced before Amber:
a) Regular engagement with employees across locations
b) Huge manual effort + Lack of culture reports
c) Loss of employee pulse after month 1 of their joining

3 Key Results after plugging in Amber:
a) Automated entire process of employee interventions
b) Increased CEO productivity + Outsourced cultural audit
c) Helped entire workforce feel heard and valued

To read more about the impact of predictive people analytics in Nearbuy's culture, visit https://goo.gl/aXNgY3

snippet.title: After Divorcing Johnny Depp For $7 Million, Amber Heard Found A New Love: Billionaire Elon Musk
snippet.description:
It seemed to be an intimate affair as they sat at a dinner table alongside each other while Amber placed her hand on the shoulder of the 45-year-old Tesla inventor and entrepreneur.
Elon Musk shared a fun Instagram picture of them at dinner in Australia with her lipstick on his cheek.
Musk reportedly 'became infatuated' with Amber after the two appeared in the 2013 film Machete Kills.
This is Heard's first time in the country since her dogs scandal in 2015 with Johnny Depp.
It caused an uproar back in the day after she illegally brought her pet dogs to the country with her ex-husband, Depp, in 2015.
In May of last year, news emerged that Johnny and Amber had called time on their relationship after 15 months of marriage. The actress was granted a restraining order after accusing him of domestic abuse.
Amber Heard looks happy with her new boyfriend, Elon Musk.
They look like they're having a great time in Australia.
Elon is also recently out of a relationship as he was granted his second divorce from Talulah Riley in November of last year. Musk has six sons with his first wife, Canadian author Justine Wilson, as they were married from 2000 to 2008.
Elon Musk and his ex-wife Talulah Riley pictured here together at the Vanity Fair Oscar Party in March 2014
The founder of Tesla and Space Exploration Technologies Corp. and CEO, Elon Musk is trying to find happiness with Amber Heard.
Musk is worth a reported $14.9 billion, according to Forbes.

snippet.title: How Amber Heard Rebounded After Her Tangled Divorce From Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
The "Aquaman" actress and billionaire post similar pictures on Instagram after recent releases of photos in Australia. Get the scoop!

After a complicated divorce from Johnny Depp nearly a year ago, Amber Heard is coming out the other side. 

Around this time last year, the 31-year-old actress was at the center of a highly publicized split from her husband of a year. However, the public barely suspected trouble in paradise until the Aquaman star filed for divorce citing "irreconcilable differences" and, two days later, was granted a domestic violence restraining order against Depp. 

"She did what she had to do to protect herself," a source told E! News at the time. "It wasn't an easy decision, but this is the truth. It was very hard for her."

snippet.title: Amber Heard Makes First Public Outing After Divorce from Johnny Depp Is Finalized
snippet.description:
Amber Heard gets by with a little help from her friends.

After her drawn-out divorce from Johnny Depp was finalized on Friday, the 30-year-old actress stepped out with some pals for a bite to eat in Los Angeles on Sunday.

Donning a black top and pants, a faded denim jacket and sunglasses, Heard stepped out of her black SUV for her first public outing since the divorce was finalized.

The Rum Diary costars became embroiled in a nasty court after the actress filed to end her 15-month marriage to Depp in May, and accused him of domestic abuse.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Was Told Coming Out as Bisexual Would ‘End My Career’
snippet.description:
Amber Heard is no stranger to her personal life playing out in public, but even she was shocked at the interest surrounding her sexual orientation when she came out as bisexual in 2010.

The 30-year-old actress spoke at The Economist‘s second-annual Pride and Prejudice Summit in New York and talked about the moment she first told a reporter the truth about her sexuality.

“I just answered honestly,” she said about her interview seven years ago with the website After Ellen. “I could tell by the look on this person’s face it was a big deal. My poor publicist. Then I realized the gravity of what I had done and why so many people — studio execs, agents, advisers — did not want this coming before my name. I became attached to a label. … So, I watched as I quickly became not actress Amber Heard but out lesbian Amber Heard.”

Apparently, the warnings by Hollywood execs carried some truth.

“It did impact my career; it was difficult,” she admitted. “It was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult, because no one had done it. … I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career without a doubt.”

However, the risk was worth it. “I’ve never seen myself defined by the person I’m with. … I saw myself being in this unique position and having a unique responsibility,” she continued. “So, I bit the bullet.”

At the time, the actress already had credits in Zombieland and Pineapple Express under her belt, and her star was on the rise.

“As a leading lady, there’s a certain amount of wish fulfillment. I was asked ‘How is anyone going to invest in you romantically if they think you’re unavailable?’” she recalled. “I said, ‘Watch me do it.’”

snippet.title: Amber Heard I was told revealing I'm bisexual would ruin my career
snippet.description:
Amber Heard: I was told revealing I'm bisexual would ruin my career

Amber Heard was told revealing she is bisexual would end her career, the actress has said.
The ex-wife of Johnny Depp said film-makers doubted whether she could play a straight woman in a romantic lead role after she spoke publicly about her sexuality seven years ago.
“It did impact my career, it was difficult,” she said at The Economist’s Pride & Prejudice event in New York.
“It was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult because no one had done it.

“I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career, without a doubt.”
Amber, 30, said she disagreed with reports that she came out as bisexual in 2010, because she had never hidden her sexuality.
“When I hear someone comment about me coming out, I think it’s funny because I was never in,” she said.
The US star said she was asked directly about her sexuality by a reporter at the time and she answered “honestly” and “off the cuff”.

“Then I realised the gravity of what I had done,” she added.
“I started to understand why so many people – studio execs, directors, advisers, agents, producers – why everyone was so adamant about this not being the label that comes before my name.
“I quickly became, not actress Amber Heard, but out lesbian Amber Heard.”
Amber was in a relationship with photographer Tasya van Ree before she began dating Johnny after meeting him on the set of 2011 film The Rum Diary.

The couple married in February 2015 but had a high-profile divorce last year amid claims of domestic abuse.
Johnny vehemently denied he had been “verbally and physically abusive” for the entirety of their four-year-relationship.
The former couple later issued a a joint statement saying there was “never any intent of physical or emotional harm”.

అలా కవర్ స్టోరీ రావటంతో జీవన విధానాన్ని అలాగే ఇంకా కొనసాగిస్తే మరిన్ని చిక్కులు తప్పవని ఇండస్ట్రీ ప్రముఖులు హెచ్చరించారని ఆమె తెలిపింది. లెస్బియన్-గే-బైసెక్సువల్-ట్రాన్స్ జెండర్ (ఎల్జీబీటీ) వర్గాలపై చిన్నచూపుందని ఆమె వాపోయింది. అప్పటినుంచి తన సినీ కెరీర్ నాశనమైందన్నారు.
.తాను జానీ డెప్, నికోలస్ కేజ్ వంటి స్టార్స్ తో నటించానని, ఆ సమయంలో ఎలా ఉండేదానినో వారినడిగి తెలుసుకోవాలని ఆమె సూచించింది.
కొందరు పనిగట్టుకుని తనపై దుష్ప్రచారం చేస్తున్నారని ఆమె ఆవేదన వ్యక్తం చేసింది. ఎంత అభివృద్ధి చెందుతున్నా, సరికొత్త ఆవిష్కరణలు వస్తున్నా..కొన్ని విషయాల్లో ఎంత వెనుకబడి ఉన్నామో చెప్పేందుకు ఎల్జీబీటీలపై ఉన్న వివక్షే నిదర్శనమని ఆమె తెలిపింది.

snippet.title: ‘Everyone told me it would end my career’: Amber Heard opens up about coming out as bisexual
snippet.description:
New Delhi, March 26 (ANI): She came out publicly about her bisexuality in 2010 and now, Amber Heard has opened up about how difficult it was. Speaking at The Economist's Pride & Prejudice event at New York, the ‘Danish Girl’ star claimed that the filmmakers doubted whether she could play a straight woman in a romantic lead, reports The Independent. Heard was quoted saying, “It was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult because no one had done it.” The 30-year-old actress added, "I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career, without a doubt." The actress also shared about her "coming out" announcement and why she never hid her sexuality. “When I hear someone comment about me coming out, I think it's funny because I was never in. Then I realised the gravity of what I had done.” On a related note, Amber Heard will be next seen in Zack Snyder’s ‘Justice League’ alongside Ben Affleck.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Recalls Coming Out as Bisexual in 2010 I Became Attached to a Label
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Recalls Coming Out as Bisexual in 2010 I Became Attached to a Label.
Amber Heard has always been queer.

But, as she said at The Economist's second annual Pride & Prejudice event in New York City Thursday, It was just not important or interesting enough to make headlines. Heard publicly discussed her sexual orientation for the first time in 2010, but to her family and friends, she was always out. I was an activist. I went to protests. Funnily enough, she added, I was never in. I was in a relationship and I never hid it and then my career and my life started to change...
In 2010, After Ellen asked Heard about her sexuality. I just answered honestly. I could tell by the look on this person's face it was a big deal. My poor publicist. Then I realized the gravity of what I had done and why so many people—studio execs, agents, advisors—did not want this coming before my name. I became attached to a label. I've never seen myself defined by the person I'm with, Heard recalled. Rather than keep that aspect of her life private, I saw myself being in this unique position and having a unique responsibility. So, I bit the bullet.

Heard was told having the word bisexual attached to her name was problematic. As a leading lady, there's a certain amount of wish fulfillment. I was asked 'How is anyone going to invest in you romantically if they think you're unavailable' she said. I said, 'Watch me do it.'
In the years since her public coming out, Heard has worked steadily, starring in The Rum Diary, Machete Kills, Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl—all while fighting for LGBTQ causes.

The Justice League actress, who finalized her divorce from Johnny Depp last year, is proud to see other actors in Hollywood coming out. I stand here now amongst many of my romantic leading lady peers who are out and fluid, Heard said. I'm one of many now, and I'm working.
If we're meant to reflect the world around us, the whole point of telling stories and reaching audiences is to challenge the status quo, to push the envelope. Not just to meet the status quo. We're in a unique position to do this, she told the audience. We need to be actively pushing.

Heard argued that women are at the forefront of the LGBTQ fight in Hollywood. If every gay man that I know personally in Hollywood came out tomorrow, then this would be a non-issue in a month. Despite the progress that's already been made, she said, We have a long way to go.

snippet.title: Amber Sherlock | julie snook | mumbrella | amber heard | channel 9
snippet.description:
Amber Sherlock | julie snook | mumbrella | amber heard | channel 9
‘Go and grab a jacket!’: Nine newsreader Amber Sherlock blasts colleague for wearing similar outfit
Nine suffered a fashion emergency when newsreader Amber Sherlock realised she was wearing a similar outfit to the guests she was about to talk to just moments before going to air.
And, in off-air footage published by Mumbrella, Sherlock can be seen letting rip at her colleague Julie Snook for daring to wear a white top like hers.
For the segment, which aired Wednesday, Sherlock was in a different studio to her guests Snook and psychologist Sandy Rea. Minutes before going to air, Sherlock looked at the video feed in the studio monitor and realised they all looked like Goldie Hawn, Diane Keaton and Bette Midler in that final scene of The First Wives Club where they all wear white and sing.“I need Julie to put a jacket on because we’re all in white. I asked her before we came on — Julie, you need to put a jacket on,” a perturbed Sherlock demanded.
As Snook began to explain she just hadn’t had time to source a jacket before going into the studio, Sherlock cut her off: “Come on, I told you two hours ago.”
Sherlock then pulled her iPhone out and informed Snook she’d personally call the Nine wardrobe department to “get something”.
Fellow guest, psychologist Sandy Rea, could hear all this going down from her studio and looked appropriately uncomfortable with the exchange.
Rea tried to defuse the problem by suggesting she’d get a jacket herself.
“You’re fine Sandy but there can’t be three of us. And I made this clear two and a half hours ago,” Sherlock shot back while angrily thumbing at her iPhone, perhaps scrolling through Portmans’ online store to buy Snook a new outfit herself.

Remaining calm, Snook tried to reason with her flustered colleague.
“Amber, if it’s an issue I can get on out of here (the studio),” she said.
“It is an issue. Go and grab a jacket,” Sherlock demanded. Snook pointed out she was actually wearing light blue and not white but this was all swings and roundabouts for Sherlock and the technicality annoyed her more.
She called out for a producer to find Snook a jacket. Any jacket. Even if they had to just rip one off Tracy Grimshaw.
The passive aggressive back-and-forth continued.
Snook: “If there’s an issue I can just head on out and get back to work because I’m flat chat, I genuinely forgot.”
Sherlock: “Fine, jump on out, if that’s what you’d like to do.”
Snook: “Amber, please, this is not the only thing I’m doing today.”
At this point, the footage cuts to black.
The next time we see Snook, she’s been strapped into a jacket.

snippet.title: God's Feminist Movement | Interview with Amber Picota
snippet.description:
Would you be shocked, offended or apathetic if I told you I haven’t had any female guests on the podcast in over 6 years? Yes that’s right, somehow six years have gone by since the last time Fire On Your Head welcomed a female guest. Not because we’re sexist, but like as I explained in the introduction, none of the people I’ve invited on the podcast in recent years have gotten back to me.

We finally break that streak and welcome author of the forthcoming book, God’s Feminist Movement, Amber Picota to the show. We discussed a lot of different things, such as:

-the pros and cons of repurposing blog content into a book,
-the challenges I faced when I published my first Kindle book
-how she scored a book contract with Destiny Image Publishers
-how her time so far in the Welton Academy also led to her going -through the Scripture with a new set of eyes to see things we’re oftentimes conditioned to accept without question.
-God’s Feminist Movement and what it is. We’ve heard a lot of prophetic voices talk about how God is turning the hearts of the fathers to the hearts of the sons, but what about… the mothers?
-Amber shares her powerful testimony
and a lot more...

Join us this week for an in-depth conversation.

Check out Amber's site at AmberPicota.com, and pre-order a copy of her book on Amazon.

Other books mentioned in the show:

Powerful & Free by Danny Silk 

Fashioned to Reign by Kris Vallotton

Normal Christianity by Jonathan Welton

Playing Second Fiddle: God's Heart for Harmony Regarding Women and the Church by Judi Peers

Detailed blog page for this episode: http://stevebremner.com/2016/03/gods-feminist-movement-interview-with-amber-picota/

snippet.title: AMBER HEARD AND JASON MOMOA ANNOUNCE ‘AQUAMAN’ HAS WRAPPED IN FUN INSTAGRAM POSTS
snippet.description:
Jason Momoa and Amber Heard took to Instagram to announce to fans that Aquaman has wrapped after 114 days.

The DC film stars Momoa as Aquaman (Arthur Curry) and Heard as his wife, Mera. Both actors will appear in November’s Justice League.

Momoa praised Heard’s performance in his touching Instagram photo where the pair are seen sharing a bottle of wine. Momoa claimed he and his onscreen wife “went through some heavy sh*t,” and went on to say how proud he was of her. Momoa also gave love to Australia, where most of the movie was shot.

Heard returned the compliments by saying it was an “amazing 7 months.” The duo definitely seemed to be enjoying their time at the wrap party.

Filming on Aquaman took place on the Gold Coast of Queensland, Australia, according to ComingSoon. Footage was also shot in Newfoundland, Sicily, Tunisia, and at Village Roadshow Studios. The film began shooting this past May.

Aquaman‘s director, James Wan, also took to social media to announce the film’s wrap. Wan is known for his movies such as The Conjuring, Furious 7, Saw, and Insidious. Aquaman will be Wan’s second film that is not classified as a scary movie or horror flick.


Aquaman also stars Nicole Kidman as Queen Atlanna, Dolph Lundgren as King Nereus, Willem Dafoe as Nuidis Vulko, and Patrick Wilson as the film’s villain, Orm (a.k.a. Ocean Master).

Arthur is the half-human son of Queen Atlanna and half-brother of Orm. According to ScreenRant, Arthur is her first born but she must leave him

snippet.title: Johnny Depp vs Amber Heard : la bataille continue !
snippet.description:
Retrouvez toutes nos exclus sur http://star24.tv
Facebook : https://www.facebook.com/pages/STAR-24-TV-100-Stars/745969692103367?fref=ts
Twitter : https://twitter.com/S24TV

Décidément, cette histoire de divorce ne finira jamais ! De nouveaux éléments ont été ajoutés dans les démarches judiciaires entre Johnny Depp et Amber Heard.

Ce n'est pas le passage à la nouvelle année qui a calmé les deux ex tourtereaux, bien au contraire...ça les a même inspiré ! En pleine séparation depuis plusieurs mois déjà, de nouveaux rebondissements ont fait surface.

D'après nos confrères de TMZ, Amber Heard a déposé de nouveaux documents juridiques à la justice américaine où l'on peut lire que son ex-mari refuse de payer les sept millions de dollars prévu dans leur accord. Selon la belle blonde, Johnny Depp n'a pas signé le papier nécessaire au versement de la somme.

Mais l'acteur ne se laisse pas faire ! Il accuse même la jeune femme de faire en sorte que le divorce ne se règle pas de sitôt pour se faire de la publicité. 

Alors Amber Heard VS Johnny Depp, qui aura le dernier mot ? La suite, au prochain épisode...

snippet.title: ‘Everyone told me it would end my career’: Amber Heard opens up about coming out as bisexual
snippet.description:
New Delhi, March 26 (ANI): She came out publicly about her bisexuality in 2010 and now, Amber Heard has opened up about how difficult it was. Speaking at The Economist's Pride & Prejudice event at New York, the ‘Danish Girl’ star claimed that the filmmakers doubted whether she could play a straight woman in a romantic lead, reports The Independent. Heard was quoted saying, “It was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult because no one had done it.” The 30-year-old actress added, "I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career, without a doubt." The actress also shared about her "coming out" announcement and why she never hid her sexuality. “When I hear someone comment about me coming out, I think it's funny because I was never in. Then I realised the gravity of what I had done.” On a related note, Amber Heard will be next seen in Zack Snyder’s ‘Justice League’ alongside Ben Affleck. 
--------------------------------------

snippet.title: Narcissistic Abuse Recorded!  **LANGUAGE, POSSIBLE TRIGGERS**
snippet.description:
NOTE: Typo.  I meant to say if Amber DID know what was bothering Johnny, why would she ask  "What happened?"  
One very important thing to observe here: Johnny Depp DID NOT hit Amber Heard in this video, nor did he throw anything at her.  He did everything he could to avoid going near her. When he realized she was filiming him, which obviously she'd done before by the conversation?  He had finally had enough and lost his temper but STILL didn't hit her.  She had what looked like a small black remote control in her hand(first look 1:00), and seemed to use it to control a camera either buried in a wall or hidden behind something.  Johnny reached for the remote in her hand but instead of grabbing her hand and wrestling with her for the remote, he went right to the camera and yanked it out of wherever it was and slammed it to the floor. The only casualties in this video were the camera, some unfortunate cabinets, a door, and several wine glasses. Maybe even a bottle.  However, no human beings were struck physically during the making of this video.  You'll see when you watch it broken down.
 It's clear that Amber has started conversations like this one with Johnny before, when he's at his angriest and clearly wants to be left alone.  No abuse victim would seek to engage their abuser in a fight, to see if they get hit, just so they can get it on tape.  It doesn't make sense.
Johnny Depp and Amber Heard were officially divorced January of 2017.  In May of 2016 after filing for divorce, she accused him of domestic violence which caused many to do battle with words on social media and otherwise.  When they settled out of court, they had a document that stated, and I will paraphrase correctly.  Their relationship, passionate and sometimes volatile was still always bound by love.  Neither party lied for financial gain and there was no intention of physical or emotional harm.  Amber wished Johnny the best and pledged to donate her spousal support to charity.
However, she also dropped the charges against Johnny with prejudice, a legal term for swearing in a court of law that she'd never refile those charges against Depp.  Also "neither lied for financial gain"(paraphrased) doesn't mean neither lied to protect a reputation!  Based on her Instagram post repeating the joint statement after JK Rowling spoke out to assure her fans that she feels comfortable with Johnny Depp in the Fantastic Beasts franchise?   Amber Heard's jumping in and responding like that shows how very concerned she is about her reputation.  Narcissists always are, but for now, I will let my breakdown of her original video speak for itself.

Many would like to be done with this chapter but unfortunately domestic violence is everyone's business.  It will never end.  Because these people are famous and no one truly was "there" except others not talking about it anymore?  We may never know or have "solid proof."  What I did was look very hard at both sides last year, as this issue is close to my heart thanks to my own experiences with abuse.  If  I saw any indication that Johnny Depp even remotely abused Amber Heard, I would not be defending him to this day.  Women, please remember that some of our fellow women are not all good.  Many are abusers, just like those men that abuse women.  Many women use feminism to their advantage, playing the victim to make a man look horrible or ruin his life.  It's sick and pathological but it happens all the time.  I am still getting many views and comments on this video, and while many can say with ease, "Let them get on with their lives!"  unfortunately once narcissists put out smear campaigns on their discarded human supply, it never stops.  Those speaking up for Amber won't stop until Johnny is boycotted.  He will never be boycotted but they are so fired up because of REAL abusers like Weinstein that they can't cool down.  Why respond, say some of you?  Well, I'm not feeding narcs, I am just continuing to put out the other side of things for the sake of discernment.  Let Truth continue to be Spoken and never Silenced!!!  Namaste to all.

Created using http://studio.stupeflix.com/

snippet.title: Amber Heard's Miami wonderland at the Delano hotel  - Travel Guide vs Booking
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching, Like, shre , comment vs Subscribe Please!
 Continuing our series on the world’s hottest hotels and the stars who frequent them, this week Sarah Turner checks out the Delano in Miami…Vital statistics: Designed by Robert Swartburg and named after the then US President, Franklin Delano Roosevelt, the Art Deco turrets of the Delano have dominated South Beach since it opened in 1947.In 1994, famed hotelier and nightclub owner Ian Schrager took the helm. With designer Philippe Starck, and using contemporary art and a party vibe, he invented this cool and aspirational boutique hotel.The 194 all-white bedrooms are so plain they could pass for a posh hospital, but they’re designed to drive people into public spaces for entertainment such as the Argentinian-tinged restaurant Leynia, or the small but chic Doheny Room, which aims for an indie 1980s club feel.Is the Delano pretentious? Yes, a little. Most hotels in Miami have a swimming pool, but the Delano has decreed that it has a water salon because most of the pool is designed to be shallow enough for guests to wade in at chest height while sipping cocktails, but it is a great deal of fun.Location report: At the corner of Collins and 17th Street, this is where South Beach’s hotels become bigger and – crucially – have gates that lead straight on to the beach.The Delano is surrounded by a clutch of luxury hotels, including SLS and The Raleigh.A tall hedge separates it from the street and keeps gawkers away. Key attraction: When Ian Schrager took over the Delano, he wanted to make hotels as exciting as nightclubs.It still takes fun very seriously. Starck looked to Alice In Wonderland for inspiration.The garden is filled with fairy lights, daybeds and giant chessboards. The pool bungalows – adored by A-listers such as Leonardo DiCaprio – are the most popular.Inside, the lobby continues the spectacle with a clear grand piano which is played, when the mood takes her, by Queen Latifah.In the news: The Delano is no longer quite as cutting-edge, but it still has a vibe that other hotels envy.The weekend pool parties have become a South Beach institution; giant inflatables and a DJ playing by the bar so that guests don’t have to leave their sunlounger.It still attracts celebrity guests – last year Johnny Depp’s ex Amber Heard checked in.Good enough for the rest of us?If you’re not staying there, the all-you-can-eat brunch is a South Beach bargain at $70 (about £53) a head, with unlimited mimosas or Bloody Marys for just $15 (£11) more.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp et Amber Heard: Retour sur un divorce chaotique et scandaleux !
snippet.description: Si le divorce de Johnny Depp et Amber Heard a fait les gros titres de la presse people, la rédac' de melty vous propose de revenir sur cette séparation plus compliquée que jamais..  . C'est la question que tout le monde se pose. Johnny Depp a-t-il fait une grave erreur en quittant Vanessa Paradis pour Amber Heard ? On vous laisse juger ! Ce qui est certain, c'est que son histoire avec la jolie blonde aura été plus chaotique jamais. Tout commence alors en 2011. Nous sommes sur le plateau de tournage du film Rhum express et l'acteur craque pour la jolie blonde. Après 14 ans de vie commune, il décide alors de se séparer de la mère de ses deux enfants, Lily-Rose et Jack Depp. Tout s'enchaîne alors très vite entre les deux tourtereaux. Malgré leur 22 ans d'écart et les quelques tensions qui commencent à faire leur apparition, le couple ne se quitte plus et se fiance en 2014. Un an plus tard, le 5 février 2015, Johnny Depp et Amber Heard se disent "oui" à Los Angeles. Pour leur lune de miel, ils s'envolent aux Bahamas sur l'île privée du comédien. Une romance qui passionne les foules ! Surtout que les deux love birds vont enchaîner les apparitions médiatiques et les preuves d'affection. Mais alors qu'on les imagine vivre une belle et longue idylle heureuse, rien ne se passe comme prévu.. Seulement quinze mois après son mariage avec Johnny Depp, Amber Head demande le divorce pour "différends irréconciliables" en plus d'une ordonnance restrictive contre l'acteur en mai 2016. Mais que s'est-il passé ? Si l'on en croit les informations relayées dans la presse américaine, l'actrice accuse son futur ex-mari de violences conjugales. À partir de cet instant, l'affaire prend un véritable tournant dramatique et devient un feuilleton ultra médiatisé. TMZ dévoile d'ailleurs des photos choc sur lesquelles la comédienne apparaît le visage couvert de bleus. La jeune femme accuse son compagnon de l'avoir frappé avec son iPhone au visage. Très vite, deux camps vont se former à Hollywood. Ceux qui soutiennent Amber Heard et ceux qui apportent leur soutien à Johnny Depp. À l'image de sa fille Lily-Rose Depp, son ex-fiancée Winona Ryder ou encore son ex-femme Vanessa Paradis qui n'hésite pas à écrire une lettre expliquant que le père de ses deux enfants n'a jamais été violent envers elle pendant leur 14 années de vie commune. Et pourtant, des SMS accablants datant de 2014 vont rapidement être dévoilés dans la presse. Dans ces derniers, la jeune femme revient sur les nombreux coups dont elle aurait été victime dans une conversation avec Stephen Deuters, l'assistant de son ex-époux. Ses messages sont-ils authentiques ? Pas si l'on en croit ce dernier qui dément avoir écrit ses textos. Ce qui est certain, c'est que plus les jours passent, plus le divorce prend de l'ampleur.. D'après les informations du magazine Closer, la dispute entre Johnny Depp et Amber Heard aurait été déclenchée par un événement bien particulier. En effet, l'acteur n'aurait apparemment pas supporté de v

snippet.title: Top 10 Celebrity Lesbians Which You Love
snippet.description:
Top 10 Celebrity Lesbians Witch You Love

10. Amber Heard
Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986)  is an American actress.
 She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights, starring Billy Bob Thornton. Her breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. 

9. Portia De Rossi 
Portia Lee James DeGeneres - Portia de Rossi is an Australian–American actress, model, and philanthropist. She currently appears as a regular cast member on the American political thriller television series Scandal in the role of Elizabeth North, the Vice President's Chief of Staff.

8.  Tila Tequila 
Thien Thanh Thi Nguyen  (born October 24, 1981), better known by her stage names Tila Tequila, Tila Nguyen and Miss Tila Born in Singapore and raised in Houston, Texas, Tequila moved to Los Angeles in 2001 to pursue her modeling career. After being featured in numerous men's magazines she made her reality television debut on the VH1 show Surviving Nugent (2003).

7. Michelle Rodriguez
Mayte Michelle Rodriguez  (July 12, 1978),  is an American actress, screenwriter, and DJ.Her breakout role was as a troubled boxer in the independent film Girlfight (2000), which was met with critical acclaim and earned her several awards, including the Independent Spirit Award and Gotham Award for Best Debut Performance

6. Anne Heche
Anne Celeste Heche (May 25, 1969) is an American actress, a director, and a screenwriter. Her film credits include Six Days, Seven Nights, Return to Paradise, I Know What You Did Last Summer, John Q and Volcano. 
She also starred in the television series Men in Trees, Hung, Save Me, Dig, and guest-starred on ABC's hit series Quantico.

5. Chely Wright
Richell Rene "Chely" Wright  (October 25, 1970) is an American country music singer and gay rights activist. On the strength of her debut album in 1994, the Academy of Country Music (ACM) named her Top New Female Vocalist in 1995. In May 2010, Wright became one of the first major country music performers to publicly come out as lesbian 

4. Adele Hanel
Adèle Haenel (born 1 January 1989) is a French actress.
She has been nominated twice for the César Award for Most Promising Actress; in 2008 for her performance in Water Lilies (2007), and in 2012 for House of Tolerance (2011).

3. Lauren Morelli
Lauren Morelli is an American writer best known for her work on the Netflix original series Orange Is the New Black. Morelli is openly lesbian, after coming out in 2014. On October 4, 2016, Morelli announced her engagement  to cast member Samira Wiley, with whom she had been in a relationship since publicly coming out.

2. Ellen DeGeneres 
Ellen Lee DeGeneres (born January 26, 1958)  is an American comedian, television host, actress, writer, and producer. During the fourth season of Ellen in 1997, she came out as a lesbian in an appearance on The Oprah Winfrey Show. In 2008, she married her longtime girlfriend Portia de Rossi.

1. Rose and Rosie
Rose Ellen Dix (born 15 June 1988) and Roseanne Elizabeth "Rosie" Spaughton (born 30 May 1990) known as Rose and Rosie are an English comedy and entertainment duo known for their popular YouTube videos. Rose proposed to Rosie on 30 May 2014 and the wedding took place in England at Clearwell Castle on 20 March 2015.

Rose Ellen Dix (born 15 June 1988) and Roseanne Elizabeth "Rosie" Spaughton (born 30 May 1990) known as Rose and Rosie are an English comedy and entertainment duo known for their popular YouTube videos. snippet.title: WAVY-TV story: Family, police address case of missing Hampton mother, daughter
snippet.description:
Story/Video from WAVY-TV 10:
HAMPTON, Va. (WAVY) — It’s a frantic search for a missing mom and baby. The Amber Alert for 8-month-old Chloe Johnson expired Thursday night, but the baby and her mother, Keir Johnson are still considered missing and in danger.

Eight-month-old Chloe Johnson and her mother, 34-year-old Keir Johnson, were reported missing earlier this month. Hampton police say the two were last seen Sunday, April 30 in the 1900 block of Hastings Drive. Johnson was heading to Buckroe Beach. No one has seen or heard from Keir since.

“My sister is somewhere where she needs help and we just haven’t found her yet,” said Johson’s twin sister Teir Pettway. “I call her hoping one day she will answer the phone.”

Pettway’s concern stretches all way to Colorado where she is now living. The last time she talked with her sister was just hours before Hampton police say she went she went missing in late April.

Police say the two were last seen Sunday, April 30 in the 1900 block of Hastings Drive. Johnson was heading to Buckroe Beach. No one has seen or heard from Keir since.

“We were just taking about normal things,” Pettway added. “I went out to eat at the restaurant and I was just telling her about my experience at the restaurant.”

Keir and Chloe have now been missing for three weeks.

Last week, state police issued an Amber Alert last week on behalf of Hampton police for Chloe. Virginia State Police announced the termination of the Amber Alert Thursday night. State Police say the alert was terminated in accordance with Amber Alert policy.

Virginia Amber Alert Plan | General Guidelines

“Standard procedures for a Virginia Amber Alert dictate a 12-hour activation period, unless there are extenuating circumstances,” Virginia State Police spokeswoman Corinne Geller said in an email Thursday night. “The Amber Alert for Chloe Johnson was originally activated May 11, 2017. Upon completion of seven days, the activation has now been terminated.”

According to Virginia’s Amber Alert website, Chloe and Keir Johnson are still considered missing and endangered.

On Monday, 10 On Your Side learned Newport News police were taking over the investigation into Chloe and Keir’s disappearance. The car police believe the two were in was recovered in Newport News on Mother’s Day morning about 10 miles from Johnson’s Hampton home.

“Our detectives on every level, special victim’s unit, homicide are working around the clock and following up on any leads that we get in this case,” said Newport News Officer Brandon Maynard.

Detectives continue to interview family and friends trying to retrace Johnson’s last steps.

“You have to rule out everything and talk to all possible witnesses and families members,” Maynard added. “That’s basic investigation.”

Thursday night, the state police cancelled the AMBER Alert. Newport News officers say that was just protocol.

(“We just want to let the public know that the Amber Alert may be cancelled, but it does not mean we are quitting all efforts in looking for Chloe and Keir Johnson,” Maynard said.

“To me, I just think somebody knows something and they just haven’t come forward yet,” Pettway added. “Everybody worries, because we just want them back safely.”

If you see Chloe or Keir or know anything about their disappearance, call Newport News police immediately at (757) 928-4100 or Virginia State Police at 1-800-822-4453.

WAVY News is working to learn more about this developing story. Stay with WAVY.com for updates as they become available.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Claims She Feared For Her Life After Johnny Depp 'Tried To Smother Her With Pillow
snippet.description:
Amber Heard claims she feared for her life after Johnny Depp 'tried to smother her with pillow

Heard said: “There was one severe ­incident in December 2015 when I truly feared for my life” 
 Amber Heard has claimed husband Johnny Depp tried to smother her with a pillow while drunk.

The actress said in legal papers: “I feared for my life.”

A pal of Amber has claimed Depp left his wife with facial injuries and a chunk of hair missing during a terrifying drunken attack.

Heard is said to have texted the pal for help after the film star allegedly tried to smother her with a pillow in a violent incident that left her “battered and bruised”.

The model and actress, 30, has released new photos showing injuries she claimed Depp inflicted on her during the alleged assault at their Los Angeles apartment in December last year.
As part of her legal action, in which she successfully applied for a restraining order, Heard said: “There was one severe ­incident in December 2015 when I truly feared for my life.”
Her friend backed her claim yesterday by saying: “I got to her apartment to find her with a cut and bruised lip, a swollen eye and a chunk of hair missing from the top of her head.

“This incident really stuck with me because she confided in me that day that she feared for her life after an intoxicated Johnny tried to suffocate her with a pillow.

“I have personally witnessed the aftermath of Johnny Depp’s violent and abusive behaviour towards her on many occasions.”

The friend’s comments in a US newspaper yesterday and the new photos in People magazine emerged just days after Heard claimed she was hit by iPhone thrown by Depp.
Last week she told a court she had not seen her husband of 15 months for about four weeks before he arrived at their home on May 21 “inebriated and high” – the day after the death of his mother, Betty Sue Palmer, 81.

After initially having a “peaceful conversation” about his mother’s death, she claimed Depp’s “demeanour changed dramatically” and he became “extremely angry”.

She said: “Johnny then grabbed the cell phone, wound up his arm like a baseball pitcher and threw the cell phone at me, striking my cheek and eye with great force.”
But despite providing pictures of her injuries, police are “adamant” they saw no marks on her when they attended the couple’s flat two weeks ago.

The officers spoke with their superiors on Tuesday afternoon and said they had no idea Depp was involved at all after the 911 call came in under the name Heard.

They said when they knocked at her door there had been a report of domestic dispute.

Heard greeted them through a crack but would not let them in.

They questioned her through the door and she said it was a simple verbal argument with her husband.

She never mentioned Hollywood star Depp, 52, by name. The officers told her they needed to make sure she was not declining help under duress, so they insisted on coming in and speaking with her.

Heard obliged, and the officers said they looked at her closely enough to determine there were no marks, swelling or bruising on her face or other exposed parts of her body.

She did not file a formal complaint at the time but her lawyers revealed this week that she had given a statement to detectives.

snippet.title: Maz Jobrani and Luenell Campbell on Amber Rose’s Bush Nude Photo, Celeb Break-Ins & Political Comedy
snippet.description:
No topic was off limits on Sway in the Morning when comedians Maz Jobrani and Luenell Campbell stopped by the show. We heard their thoughts about Amber Rose’s ‘bring back the bush’ Instagram pic, perceptions of sexuality in America and so much more.

We talked to Jobrani about his experience in the CBS sitcom 'Superior Donuts.' The Iranian-American comedian also spoke to us about being unapologetic about his political opinions during this sensitive climate.

We also got to hear from Campbell about her nude photoshoot for Penthouse Magazine. She tells us that she relished the opportunity to empower women her age. In fact, her goal is to see one of those photos on New York’s jumbotron when she get’s her Netflix special.

snippet.title: Actress Amber Tamblyn Says All Men Deserve To Feel “Afraid, Disoriented And Discounted”
snippet.description:
Actress Amber Tamblyn Says All Men Deserve To Feel “Afraid, Disoriented And Discounted”
Subscribe HERE For More News:https://goo.gl/hkMKQ2
Read Original Article Here:https://goo.gl/t4Vfxt

More and more, Hollywood and the liberal media has expressed their absolute hatred toward white people, men, Conservatives and Christians. In the wake of all the sexual assault allegations in Hollywood, the media and congress famous actress Amber Tamblyn wrote an op-ed for the New York Times called “I’m Not Ready for the Redemption of Men.”

In the article she dismisses the idea that innocent men can be accused, and the idea that ‘due process’ is important.

“Not everyone in my industry is in support of how quickly things are moving. There’s a lot of collateral-damage dread, a cloud of unease that has covered the industry lately with talk of potentially harmful side effects of such decisive actions. What if an innocent man is falsely accused? What if the repercussion doesn’t fit the crime? What ever happened to innocent until proved guilty?” she writes.

After explaining that those things aren’t important, she claims that ‘men’ deserve to feel ‘afraid, disoriented, and discounted.’

“They want us to leave poor Al Franken and his harmless grabbing alone. I’ve heard several male friends talk about text chains they are on with other men only; they describe it as a safe space to talk about how they feel in this moment. They feel afraid, disoriented and discounted. And I understand their need for such comfort and security. I am a woman. I know nothing other than needing such comfort and security, for my entire life. We’re in the midst of a reckoning. It’s what toxic masculinity’s own medicine tastes like,” she wrote.
snippet.tags: ['Actress Amber Tamblyn Says All Men Deserve To Feel “Afraid', 'Disoriented And Discounted”']

snippet.title: Johnny Depp, un tacle d’Amber Heard qui veut détruire sa carrière : Zapping TV 2018 - Halk Tarjel
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp, un tacle d’Amber Heard qui veut détruire sa carrière : Zapping TV 2018 - Halk Tarjel
Johnny Depp, un tacle d’Amber Heard qui veut détruire sa carrière
Amber Heard semble très mobilisée pour détruire la carrière de Johnny Depp, sur lequel elle a balancé sur Instagram, en laissant ainsi entendre que celui-ci a été violent avec elle durant leur relation qui aura duré quatre ans.


La jolie blonde s’est en effet emparée de sa page Instagram pour dénoncer l’attitude des
studios «Warner Bros» qui ont défendu l’acteur hollywoodien en le maintenant au casting d’Animaux Fantastiques.
Dans un communiqué, la production expliquait, en parlant des accusations de violences conjugales portées contre l’ex chéri de Vanessa Paradis qu’il « n’y a jamais eu d’intention de préjudice physique ou émotionne».

Amber Heard est sortie de ses gonds pour dénoncer cette formule.

«Pour être précis, c’était notre déclaration commune COMPLETE. Choisir certaines lignes et les citer en dehors de leur contexte n’est pas juste. Mesdames, continuez à vous lever et à rester fortes. Love. Amber», a-t-elle lancé. #Halk_Tarjel #Zapping_TV_2018 #Zapping_TV 

Subscribe & More Videos: https://goo.gl/VndmZ7
Thank for watching, Please Like Share And SUBSCRIBE!!!
#halktarjel2018, #

snippet.title: Amber Heard Reveals The Two Charities To Which She'll Donate Full $7m Johnny Depp Settlement
snippet.description:
Amber Heard reveals the two charities to which she'll donate FULL $7m Johnny Depp settlement 

One of the charities has a particular focus to help stop violence against women 
 Amber Heard is donating the full $7million Johnny Depp divorce settlement to charity.

Earlier this week, Johnny Depp agreed to pay his estranged wife the huge sum of money just one day before they were due to battle it out in court.

On Thursday, a statement from the actress said the money "played no role" to her and she will be donating the entire sum equally between two charities.

One of the charities is the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU), which she says has a particular focus to stop violence against women, and the other is Children’s Hospital of Los Angeles where she worked as a volunteer for the past 10 years.

The statement said: "As described in the restraining order and divorce settlement, money played no role for me personally and never has, except to the extent that I could donate it to charity and, in doing so, hopefully help those less able to defend themselves.
As reported in the media, the amount received in the divorce was $7 million and $7 million is being donated. This is over and above any funds that I have given away in the past and will continue to give away in the future."

The statement finished: "I know these organizations will put the funds to good use and look forward to continuing to support them in the future. Hopefully, this experience results in a positive change in the lives of people who need it the most.
Legal documents were filed on Tuesday in which the Rum Dairy actress withdrew her request for a restraining order.

Johnny and Amber split in May and the actress was granted a restraining order after accusing him of domestic abuse.

Amber alleged Johnny threw a phone at her during an argument and insisted there were other instances where he had been violent towards her but she filed court papers to dismiss her domestic violence case against the actor once they agreed on the settlement.
The insider added: "Initially, being the stubborn people they are, they both didn't want to give in to each other's requests. For a long time, Amber lived with a lot of hurt and had been deeply affected by Johnny's behaviour, but chose not to say anything. Whenever something would happen, he'd apologise, and they'd move on. Johnny never wanted the world to know any of this."

Amber, 30 and Johnny, 53, said in a joint statement: "Our relationship was intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love. Neither party has made false accusations for financial gain.

"There was never any intent of physical or emotional harm. Amber wishes the best for Johnny in the future. Amber will be donating financial proceeds from the divorce to a charity."

snippet.title: Amber Heard posts topless Insta pic from Bali vacation
snippet.description: American actress Amber Heard has landed in Bali and there are pics to prove iteven a topless one.  Dont get too excited though, the 31-year-old ex-wife of Johnny Depp kept it tasteful and just posed in her bikini bottoms at what appears to be a private rooftop pool, with her back to the camera, simply captioning the shot, When in Bali. A post shared by Amber Heard (@amberheard) on Sep 11, 2017 at 7:22am PDTApparently recovering from her recent breakup from billionaire boyfriend Elon Musk, Heard is accompanied in Bali by close friend Raquel Pennington and assistant, Savannah McMillan. Theres a video of Heard and Pennington donning matching white outfits, getting their groove on to some Balinese beats, with the two swinging their hips to the music.  Indonesian Instagrammers seem thrilled to see Heard in the archipelago nation, with a number of comments on her video reading Welcome to Bali!. Hello Bali!A post shared by Amber Heard (@amberheard) on Sep 10, 2017 at 8:03am PDTIn the same outfits, the two pose in a black and white shot, and another photo posted to Heards account shows them eating sashimi.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp thanks fans for trust and support at People's Choice awards
snippet.description:
The actor Johnny Depp has thanked the public for their support in the wake of his divorce from Amber Heard, a few days after proceedings were finalised.

Depp, who picked up the favourite movie icon prize at the ceremony, whose winners are voted for by the public, said he had attended the ceremony “for you, the people, who through whatever good times or bad have stood by me and trusted me”.

Depp, who has picked up 13 previous People’s Choice gongs, continued: “And you’ve graciously invited me here once again tonight, so I appreciate that so much. You have no idea how much I appreciate that.

snippet.title: Cara Delevingne Accepts Amber Heard's Award at Unite4: Humanity Gala
snippet.description:
Amber Heard had to leave the Unite4: Humanity Gala early due to an emergency but luckily her friend Cara Delevingne was there to accept her award!

Earlier in the night, the duo stepped out on the red carpet at the annual gala on Friday (April 7) at the Beverly Wilshire Four Seasons Hotel in Beverly Hills, Calif.

When it came time for Amber to be honored for her humanitarian work with the American Civil Liberties Union, she had unfortunately already left.

“Our dear friend Amber unfortunately suffered a bit of an emergency earlier this evening and she had to go,” her friend iO Tillett Wright said on stage with Cara, according to E! News.

iO added, “And I want to also say that I’ve never seen Amber nervous and I’ve known her quite intimately for a long time. And she’s met pretty much everyone that you could be starstruck by. But Ayaan Hirsi Ali is as close to God as you could get for her, so to know that Ayaan was here and for her to have to leave anyway means that it was a very serious emergency. We both are hoping that she’s okay.”

We hope everything is okay with Amber as well!
snippet.tags: ['Amber Heard', 'Unite4: Humanity Gala', 'Cara Delevingne', 'iO Tillett Wright', 'E! News', 'Ayaan Hirsi Ali']

snippet.title: Bang - Amber Heard, il nuovo amore è lui! Ecco la conferma
snippet.description:
(KIKA) - LOS ANGELES - Amber Heard ha confermato la relazione con Elon Musk, imprenditore  visionario e fondatore della Tesla. Le voci e i rumor, che vanno avanti dallo scorso luglio, sono stati finalmente confermati  su Instagram da uno scatto dell'attrice e modella, che si trovava a cena con Musk in un ristorante australiano.

GUARDA IL VIDEO Johnny Depp è al verde per le sue spese folli

I due appaiono a tavola con due calici di vino. Amber Heard che ha postato l'immagine, ha stampato un'inequivocabile impronta di rossetto con un bacio sulla guancia del fidanzato.

 Elon Musk guida l'ipotetica rivoluzione delle auto elettriche. È stato sposato dal 2000 al 2008 con la scrittrice canadese Justine Musk, da cui ha avuto due figli.

snippet.title: Amber Heard and Elon Musk in Chile together
snippet.description:
PICTURED: Amber Heard and Elon Musk enjoy festive trip to Chile together as on-again couple are pictured having dinner with pals.
Amber Heard and Elon Musk are enjoying a festive getaway to Chile together.

The 31-year-old actress and the Tesla CEO began dating in 2016 before parting ways in August this year, and although they recently denied a reconciliation, the pair have been spotted vacationing together in South America.

In a photo obtained by Dailymail.com the reunited couple are seen dining with family - including Elon's brother Kimbal - and friends near Santiago, Chile.

The picture was shared by an Instagram account named El Taringa and shows Amber in a black dress and tan wide-brim fedora gazing down at her phone.

snippet.title: Gal Gadot e Amber Heard, gara di bellezza per Justice League
snippet.description:
(KIKA) - LOS ANGELES - Una splendida Amber Heard si è presa la scena sul red carpet della premiere di Justice League, il nuovo film diretto da Zack Snyder e Josh Whedon che sarà ambientato nei momenti immediatamente successivi alle vicende narrate in Batman vs Superman: Dawn of Justice e uscirà in italia il 16 novembre.

L'ex compagna di Johnny Depp e Elon Musk si è presentata sul tappeto rosso con un lungo abito della collezione Versace che in quanto a sensualità ha dato del filo da torcere a Gal Gadot, in oro firmata Altuzarra Spring 2018 RTW

La pellicola ha riportato sul set il trio composto da Ben Affleck nei panni di Batman, Henry Cavill in quelli di Superman e la bellissima Gal Gadot alias Wonder Woman. Accanto a loro, lotterà uno squadrone di fedelissimi DC, composto da Aquaman, interpretato da Jason Momoa, Flash impersonato da Ezra Miller e Ray Fisher nelle vesti di Cyborg.

snippet.title: Amber Heard gets racy at GQ Men of the Year aw ards
snippet.description:
'I accept this award on behalf of my dogs': Bisexual actress Amber Heard punches the air victoriously at GQ awards after applauding Australia's yes vote on same sex-marriage... as she's named Woman of the Year.
She's the former wife of Johnny Depp, who was once prosecuted for illegally bringing her dogs to Australia.

And having touched down again in Australia on Wednesday, Amber Heard made a triumphant entrance at the GQ Men of the Year awards in Sydney - and joked about her and her ex-husband's infamous quarantine case.

Amber, who had earlier revealed her joy at the results of the Australian same-sex marriage postal vote, on Instagram, punched her fist in the air with joy as she arrived at the VIP event.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard finalise divorce
snippet.description:
The divorce of film star Johnny Depp and actress Amber Heard has been finalised after months of wrangling over the final terms of the break up.

Depp, 53, has agreed to pay Heard $7m (£5.6m; €6.6m), which she says she will donate to two charities.

Heard, 30, will get to keep the couple's dogs, Pistol and Boo, who were at the centre of scandal when she took them to Australia illegally in 2015.

She had accused Depp of domestic abuse - a claim he denies. 

According to court documents, she said Depp had been physically abusive to her, culminating in him throwing a mobile phone at her face during a fight in February last year. 




Depp's lawyer denied the allegations, saying Heard was "attempting to secure a premature financial resolution by alleging abuse". Police officers attending the scene said they had found no evidence of a crime.
The actress had filed for a restraining order, but this was dropped after the majority of the terms of the divorce were settled in August.

But the divorce was only finalised this week because lawyers could not agree over whether Depp should make the payments directly to the charities or not.


Divorce settlement - who gets what?
◾Depp to pay Heard $7m (£5.6m; €6.6m)
◾Heard to keep dogs Pistol and Boo, and a horse called Arrow
◾Depp to retain sole possession of real estate assets, including properties in LA, Paris and his private island in the Bahamas
◾He will also keep more than 40 vehicles and vessels, including vintage cars and motorcycle collection
◾Heard to drop request for continued restraining order against Depp
◾Confidentiality provision prevents them from discussing relationship publicly
◾No spousal support for either actor


Heard said she would donate the money from the divorce settlement to the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) and the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles.

Her lawyer, Pierce O'Donnell, said it was a "great day" for his client, adding: "All Amber wanted was to be divorced and now she is."
◾Heard and Depp row over divorce money
◾Depp and Heard reach divorce settlement
◾Johnny Depp and Amber Heard to divorce

Depp's lawyer, Laura Wasser, said they were "all pleased to put this unpleasant chapter in Mr Depp and his family's lives behind them".

The couple, who have no children together, were married for just under 18 months when they split in May 2016.

AMBER HEARD - Sie knutscht mit einem Unbekannten
Mit Johnny Depp (54, "Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas") und Elon Musk (46) kann Amber Heard (31) zwei der berühmtesten - beziehungsweise einflussreichsten - Männer der Welt zu ihren Ex-Lieben zählen. Nur wenige Wochen nachdem die Trennung von Investor und Philanthrop Musk bekannt wurde, ist nun ein leidenschaftliches Video von Heard aufgetaucht.

Video zeigt Amber Heard mit Unbekanntem
Eines, das zu belegen scheint, dass sie erst einmal genug von prominenten Männern hat. In dem 23 Sekunden langen Clip, den offenbar jemand zufällig mit seiner Handykamera gemacht hat und der bei der "New York Post" zu sehen ist, knutscht Heard wild mit einem mysteriösen Unbekannten.

Wer ist der unbekannte Mann?
Auch die US-Kollegen konnten bislang nicht ausmachen, um wen es sich bei dem muskulösen, oberkörperfreien Mann handelt. Im kurzen Video aber scheint Heard kaum ihre Finger (beziehungsweise Zunge) von dem Herren lassen zu können. Aufgenommen wurde der Clip demnach in Australien. Von einer Quelle soll zudem berichtet worden sein, dass auf dem Nachbargrundstück von Heards Bleibe gerade eine Hausbesichtigung stattfand, als offenbar ein Interessent mehr zu sehen bekam, als nur ein leerstehendes Haus.

snippet.title: 'Fantastic Beasts' director David Yates defends Johnny Depp despite Amber Heard’s abuse accusations
snippet.description:
'Fantastic Beasts' director David Yates defends keeping Johnny Depp despite Amber Heard’s abuse accusations

Johnny Depp appears at the end of Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them as the villainous Grindelwald, and will have a larger role in the sequel, an unsettling prospect for many considering the domestic abuse allegations leveled against him by his ex-wife Amber Heard. The two reached a settlement after her suit, and issued a statement that read “our relationship was intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love. Neither party has made false accusations for financial gains.” Despite a Hollywood climate that has recently cracked down on abusive men in power such as Harvey Weinstein, director David Yates told Entertainment Weekly that he has no concerns about working with Depp. “Honestly, there’s an issue at the moment where there’s a lot of people being accused of things, they’re being accused by multiple victims, and it’s compelling and frightening,” Yates said. “With Johnny, it seems to me there was one person who took a pop at him and claimed something. I can only tell you about the man I see every day: He’s full of decency and kindness, and that’s all I see. Whatever accusation was out there doesn’t tally with the kind of human being I’ve been working with.”


Yates also noted that Depp’s exes, including Winona Ryder, have spoken positively of him. “By testament, some of the women in [Depp’s] life have said the same thing — ‘that’s not the human being we know,’” Yates said. “It’s very different [than cases] where there are multiple accusers over many years that need to be examined and we need to reflect on our industry that allows that to roll on year in and year out. Johnny isn’t in that category in any shape or form. So to me, it doesn’t bear any more analysis. It’s a dead issue.”

snippet.title: Amber Heard Net Worth
snippet.description: Amber Heard is an actress that was born in Austin, Texas, on April 22, 1986. Heard began dating Johnny Depp in 2012. They would get married in a secret ceremony on February 4, 2017. Heard and Depp currently do not have any children together. After appearing in several music videos, Amber Heard got her film career started in 2004 when she earned a small role in the film "Friday Night Lights." She would quickly earn small roles in the films "North Country" and "Alpha Dog." After accepting small film and television roles for four years, Amber Heard would get her first major roles in 2008 in "Never Back Down" and "Pineapple Express." Thanks to the exposure gained from these two films, Amber Heard's acting career was starting to take off. She officially became a major star in 2011 when she earned starring roles in the films "Drive Angry" and "The Rum Diary." Heard would also get a starring role on the short-lived television show "The Playboy Club" in 2011. She was able to use her new success to earn roles in "Paranoia," "3 Days to Kill," "Machete Kills" and "Magic Mike XXL." Amber Heard currently has an estimated net worth of $4.5 million. Almost all of Heard's net worth was acquired from her film career. She did a total of four films in 2013 and 2014.
